Key Match Events: Match No.26 of T20 World Cup 2022 between England and Australia on Friday, October 28 had to be abandoned due to rain without a single ball being bowled.
At 15:18 IST, the match was abandoned, thereby leading England and Australia to share one point apiece.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Melbourne has been experiencing heavy rainfall and it’s the second match on the day that couldn't take place at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.
Earlier in the day, the Super 12 Group 1 match between Ireland and Afghanistan couldn’t take place due to relentless rain.
The British team is currently placed second in the points table with a net run rate of 0.239.
The Aussies are fourth in the table with a net run rate of -1.555.
While England beat the Afghans in their first game, the Aussies secured a victory against Sri Lanka following their loss at the hands of Kane Williamson's New Zealand.
The Black Caps remain at the top of the points table with three points and a net run rate of 4.450.
Afghanistan, led by Mohammad Nabi, have been hard done by after both their previous two matches couldn't take place due to indifferent weather in Australia.
